	In July 2007, I had opened two recurring deposit accounts with ICICI Bank, one in my daughter rsquo;s name and the other in my son rsquo;s name. The term of the deposits was five years and the annual interest payable was 10 per cent. I have been depositing Rs 1,000 per month. But apart from pay-in slips, I have no other documents from the bank stating that my deposits are earning a 10 per cent interest for five years. Despite repeated requests the bank has not given me a passbook or a certificate against the deposit. What should I do?
    
	Jayasree Mitra, Calcutta    You make a written application to the bank asking them to issue you passbooks against the two recurring deposits. Keep a copy of the application acknowledging the receipt by the bank. Wait for a month. If the bank doesn rsquo;t reply or the replies are not to your satisfaction, approach the banking ombudsman at the Reserve Bank office on N.S. Road.
