    I purchased a house in Bhowanipur in 2005. I decided to sell it after some litigation arose. I believe that I shall have to pay tax on the selling amount. Please advise me different savings instruments that come without risks. 
    
	S. Nag, Calcutta  You shall have to pay tax on the long-term capital gains, if you have one, on the sale of the house. In our Personal Finance column, we keep on discussing various tax-exempt investment instruments from where you can get a reasonable return at lower risks. Keep watching this column.
    No need to declare
    Investment up to Rs 1 lakh in the Senior Citizen Savings Scheme is non-taxable under Section 80C of the Income Tax Act, provided the principal amount is not withdrawn before five years. But the form for such investment doesn rsquo;t contain any such declaration by the investor. Is declaration necessary? 
    
	Sunil Chandra Kar, Calcutta  Declaration is not necessary. For example, when you take a home loan, the tax benefit is available if the loan is not repaid in full within five years. What it means is that you shall not get the tax benefit that you might have claimed earlier had you withdrawn the amount within five years.   If you have any queries about investing or taxes or a high-cost purchase you are planning, mail to: btgraph@abpmail.com, or write to: Business Telegraph, 6 Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta 700 001.                                                                                                                                                                                                    
